docs.abstract: The grocery chain’s “Whole Paycheck” reputation doesn’t appear to be threatened.
docs.snippet: The grocery chain’s “Whole Paycheck” reputation doesn’t appear to be threatened.
docs.lead_paragraph: After buying Whole Foods in 2017, Amazon made a couple of bold pronouncements about lowering prices at the grocery chain. It made a third this week, saying that it was offering lower prices on hundreds of items, especially fresh produce, without going into much detail. It is also giving more special discounts to people signed up for Prime, the company’s membership service.

headline.main: Whole Foods Cut Prices. It Saved Us 5 Cents.
headline.print_headline: Whole Foods Delivers on Its Promised Price Cut. We Saved 5 Cents.

docs.abstract: Deap Ubhi has spent his tech career bouncing around. Now he’s tangled up in a little battle over one of the biggest government I.T. contracts in history.
docs.snippet: Deap Ubhi has spent his tech career bouncing around. Now he’s tangled up in a little battle over one of the biggest government I.T. contracts in history.
docs.lead_paragraph: Deap Ubhi is a restless guy. At 26, he quit his job in private equity in Northern California, where he had grown up and gone to college, and then moved to India to found Burrp!, a local search site similar to Yelp. He sold the company in 2009 and along with other alums became what they called the Burrp! mafia, seeding and growing other start-ups in India.

docs.snippet: The company also said it would lobby the federal government for a higher minimum wage.
docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — Amazon said on Tuesday that it would raise the minimum wage to $15 an hour for its United States employees, a rare acknowledgment that it was feeling squeezed by political pressure and a tight labor market. The raises apply for part-time workers and those hired through temporary agencies.
